  "texts": [
    "which is equivalent to the sum of two DRW kernels.",
    "EzTaoX models interband lags in multiband light curves using a Dirac delta transfer function, a simplified approach compared to methods that adopt more flexible transfer functions with finite width and skewed shapes (e.g., Zu et al. 2011; Starkey et al. 2016; Li et al. 2016; Donnan et al. 2021).",
    "While more sophisticated transfer functions can provide additional insights into the geometry and physical properties of AGN accretion disks (e.g., Cackett et al. 2007; Starkey et al. 2016; Fagin et al. 2024), we argue that the cadence of LSST WFD light curves is likely insufficient to resolve the detailed shape of the transfer functions.",
    "Thus, the simplified Dirac delta transfer function adopted by EzTaoX is likely adequate for lag estimation from LSST WFD light curves.",
    "Furthermore, previous investigations and the results of Section 3.2 show that even with high-cadence continuum reverberation mapping data, the use of more flexible transfer functions does not necessarily result in significantly different mean lag estimates compared to simpler methods (e.g., Fausnaugh et al. 2018; Donnan et al. 2023)."
  ],
